  "output": "## Test Coverage Analysis — jobsquare\n\n**Current state: 0% coverage.** There is no `tests/` directory, no pytest config, and `requirements.txt` only lists `httpx` and `PyYAML` — pytest itself isn't a dependency. Every function below is completely untested.\n\n### Recommended test setup (not yet present)\n\n```\n# requirements-dev.txt\npytest>=8.0\npytest-asyncio>=0.24\nrespx>=0.21          # mocks httpx at the transport level — fits the injectable-client design\nfreezegun>=1.5        # for _now()/datetime.now() determinism\n```\n\n```ini\n# pytest.ini\n[pytest]\nasyncio_mode = auto\n```\n\nSuggested layout: `tests/test_models.py`, `tests/test_filters.py`, `tests/test_store.py`, `tests/test_pipeline.py`, `tests/test_notify.py`, `tests/test_fetchers.py`, `tests/test_agent.py`.\n\n---\n\n### 1. `models.py` — untested: `parse_posted_at`, `Job.key`, `Job.posted_dt`, `Job.content_hash`, `Job.to_row`\n\nGaps:\n- Epoch-seconds vs. epoch-milliseconds branch (`>= 1e12`) is a fragile heuristic — untested at the boundary.\n- Negative epochs (`lstrip(\"-\").isdigit()`) — untested path.\n- `Z`-suffixed ISO strings, ISO without timezone (should default to UTC), and genuinely malformed strings.\n- Empty/`None` input to `parse_posted_at`.\n- `content_hash` stability/sensitivity — does it change when title changes but not when `raw` changes?\n- `to_row()` drops `raw` and adds `key`/`content_hash` — never verified.\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\nclass TestParsePostedAt:\n    def test_empty_and_none_return_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"\") is None\n        assert parse_posted_at(None) is None\n\n    def test_epoch_seconds(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1700000000\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_epoch_milliseconds_lever_style(self):\n        # 13-digit ms epoch must be divided by 1000, not treated as seconds\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332430\")\n        assert dt.year == 2022\n\n    def test_epoch_boundary_just_under_1e12_treated_as_seconds(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"999999999999\")  # 1 less than 1e12\n        assert dt.year < 2001 or dt.year > 33000  # documents current (possibly wrong) behavior\n\n    def test_negative_epoch(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"-100\")\n        assert dt is not None\n\n    def test_iso8601_with_z_suffix(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_iso8601_naive_defaults_to_utc(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_unparseable_prose_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"Posted 3 Days Ago\") is None\n\n    def test_garbage_string_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"not-a-date\") is None\n\n\nclass TestJob:\n    def _job(self, **kw):\n        base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                    title=\"SWE\", url=\"http://x\")\n        base.update(kw)\n        return Job(**base)\n\n    def test_key_is_stable_composite(self):\n        assert self._job().key == \"greenhouse:acme:1\"\n\n    def test_posted_dt_delegates_to_parse_posted_at(self):\n        assert self._job(posted_at=\"\").posted_dt is None\n\n    def test_content_hash_changes_on_title_change(self):\n        j1, j2 = self._job(title=\"SWE I\"), self._job(title=\"SWE II\")\n        assert j1.content_hash != j2.content_hash\n\n    def test_content_hash_ignores_posted_at_and_salary(self):\n        j1 = self._job(posted_at=\"2024-01-01\", salary_range=\"$100k\")\n        j2 = self._job(posted_at=\"2024-02-01\", salary_range=\"$200k\")\n        assert j1.content_hash == j2.content_hash  # documents current (possibly surprising) behavior\n\n    def test_to_row_drops_raw_adds_key_and_hash(self):\n        row = self._job(raw={\"secret\": \"x\"}).to_row()\n        assert \"raw\" not in row\n        assert row[\"key\"] == \"greenhouse:acme:1\"\n        assert \"content_hash\" in row\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `filters.py` — untested: `match`, `filter_jobs`, `_compile`\n\nGaps:\n- Word-boundary regex semantics (`\\b`) — does `\"eng\"` incorrectly match inside `\"engineering\"`? Does it correctly match `\"Eng\"` as a whole word?\n- exclude takes precedence over include when both match.\n- Case-insensitivity.\n- Empty/`None` `include`/`exclude`/`locations` lists → no filtering.\n- Location matching is substring, not exact — `\"New York\"` matches `\"New York City\"` but does `\"York\"` alone over-match?\n- Cutoff: jobs with **unparseable** `posted_at` must be kept (the “drop only when confirmed” comment is a real behavioral guarantee, currently unverified).\n- `max_age_days` accepts fractional days (`float(max_age)`), and `filter_jobs` with no `filters` dict keys at all.\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom models import Job\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\n\ndef job(**kw):\n    base = dict(source=\"x\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Software Engineer\",\n                url=\"u\", location=\"New York, NY\", department=\"Engineering\")\n    base.update(kw)\n    return Job(**base)\n\nclass TestMatch:\n    def test_no_rules_matches_everything(self):\n        assert match(job()) is True\n\n    def test_include_keyword_word_boundary_no_substring_match(self):\n        # \"eng\" should NOT match inside \"Engineering\" due to \\b\n        assert match(job(title=\"Engineering Manager\"), include=[\"eng\"]) is False\n\n    def test_include_keyword_whole_word_match(self):\n        assert match(job(title=\"Senior Engineer\"), include=[\"Engineer\"]) is True\n\n    def test_include_is_case_insensitive(self):\n        assert match(job(title=\"senior engineer\"), include=[\"Engineer\"]) is True\n\n    def test_exclude_beats_include_when_both_match(self):\n        j = job(title=\"Staff Software Engineer Manager\")\n        assert match(j, include=[\"Engineer\"], exclude=[\"Manager\"]) is False\n\n    def test_locations_substring_match(self):\n        assert match(job(location=\"New York, NY\"), locations=[\"New York\"]) is True\n\n    def test_locations_no_match(self):\n        assert match(job(location=\"Austin, TX\"), locations=[\"New York\"]) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_drops_old_confirmed_date(self):\n        old = job(posted_at=(datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)).isoformat())\n        assert match(old, cutoff=datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=7)) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_keeps_unparseable_date(self):\n        j = job(posted_at=\"Posted 3 Days Ago\")  # Workday-style prose, unparseable\n        assert match(j, cutoff=datetime.now(timezone.utc)) is True\n\n    def test_cutoff_keeps_blank_posted_at(self):\n        assert match(job(posted_at=\"\"), cutoff=datetime.now(timezone.utc)) is True\n\nclass TestFilterJobs:\n    def test_max_age_days_builds_cutoff(self):\n        stale = job(external_id=\"1\", posted_at=(datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=10)).isoformat())\n        fresh = job(external_id=\"2\", posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat())\n        result = filter_jobs([stale, fresh], {\"max_age_days\": 7})\n        assert [j.external_id for j in result] == [\"2\"]\n\n    def test_fractional_max_age_days(self):\n        result = filter_jobs([job()], {\"max_age_days\": 0.5})\n        assert isinstance(result, list)\n\n    def test_empty_rules_passthrough(self):\n        assert filter_jobs([job(), job(external_id=\"2\")], {}) == [job(), job(external_id=\"2\")]\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `store.py` — untested entirely: schema creation, migration, `diff`, `next_seq`, `added_since`\n\nThis is the most critical gap — it's the dedup source of truth. Bugs here silently corrupt \"what's new.\"\n\nGaps:\n- New job → inserted, appears in `new`.\n- Same job, same content → appears in neither `new` nor `changed`, but `last_seen` is bumped.\n- Same job, changed title/location/url/department → appears in `changed`, row updated.\n- Migration path: opening a DB created *before* `salary_range` existed shouldn't crash (`_migrate`).\n- `next_seq` starts at 1, increments monotonically, per-key independent counters.\n- `added_since` ordering and strict `>` (not `>=`) boundary — the doc comment says \"strictly after.\"\n- `get_meta`/`set_meta` upsert (`ON CONFLICT`) behavior.\n- Context manager (`__enter__`/`__exit__`) closes the connection.\n- Using `:memory:` or a tmp file across `Store` instances (state doesn't leak between fresh files).\n\n```python\nimport sqlite3\nimport pytest\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom models import Job\nfrom store import Store\n\ndef job(**kw):\n    base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"SWE\",\n                url=\"http://x\", location=\"NY\")\n    base.update(kw)\n    return Job(**base)\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef store(tmp_path):\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"test.db\") as s:\n        yield s\n\nclass TestDiff:\n    def test_new_job_is_new_not_changed(self, store):\n        new, changed = store.diff([job()])\n        assert [j.key for j in new] == [\"greenhouse:acme:1\"]\n        assert changed == []\n\n    def test_unchanged_job_on_second_run_is_neither(self, store):\n        store.diff([job()])\n        new, changed = store.diff([job()])\n        assert new == [] and changed == []\n\n    def test_last_seen_bumped_on_unchanged_rerun(self, store):\n        store.diff([job()])\n        row1 = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT last_seen FROM jobs WHERE key=?\",\n                                   (\"greenhouse:acme:1\",)).fetchone()\n        store.diff([job()])\n        row2 = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT last_seen FROM jobs WHERE key=?\",\n                                   (\"greenhouse:acme:1\",)).fetchone()\n        assert row2[\"last_seen\"] >= row1[\"last_seen\"]\n\n    def test_title_change_is_detected_as_changed(self, store):\n        store.diff([job(title=\"SWE I\")])\n        new, changed = store.diff([job(title=\"SWE II\")])\n        assert new == []\n        assert [j.title for j in changed] == [\"SWE II\"]\n\n    def test_salary_change_alone_is_not_detected(self, store):\n        # content_hash excludes salary_range — documents current behavior\n        store.diff([job(salary_range=\"$100k\")])\n        new, changed = store.diff([job(salary_range=\"$200k\")])\n        assert new == [] and changed == []\n\n    def test_first_seen_preserved_across_updates(self, store):\n        store.diff([job(title=\"SWE I\")])\n        first = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs WHERE key=?\",\n                                    (\"greenhouse:acme:1\",)).fetchone()[\"first_seen\"]\n        store.diff([job(title=\"SWE II\")])\n        after = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs WHERE key=?\",\n                                    (\"greenhouse:acme:1\",)).fetchone()[\"first_seen\"]\n        assert first == after\n\nclass TestMigration:\n    def test_opens_pre_salary_range_schema_without_crashing(self, tmp_path):\n        db = tmp_path / \"old.db\"\n        conn = sqlite3.connect(db)\n        conn.executescript(\"\"\"\n            CREATE TABLE jobs (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT, company TEXT,\n                external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT,\n                department TEXT, employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT,\n                content_hash TEXT, first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT);\n        \"\"\")\n        conn.commit(); conn.close()\n        with Store(db) as s:\n            cols = {r[\"name\"] for r in s.conn.execute(\"PRAGMA table_info(jobs)\")}\n            assert \"salary_range\" in cols\n\nclass TestMeta:\n    def test_get_meta_missing_key_returns_none(self, store):\n        assert store.get_meta(\"nope\") is None\n\n    def test_set_then_get_meta_roundtrip(self, store):\n        store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v1\")\n        assert store.get_meta(\"k\") == \"v1\"\n\n    def test_set_meta_upserts_existing_key(self, store):\n        store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v1\")\n        store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v2\")\n        assert store.get_meta(\"k\") == \"v2\"\n\nclass TestNextSeq:\n    def test_starts_at_one(self, store):\n        assert store.next_seq(\"counter\") == 1\n\n    def test_increments(self, store):\n        store.next_seq(\"counter\")\n        assert store.next_seq(\"counter\") == 2\n\n    def test_independent_counters_per_key(self, store):\n        store.next_seq(\"a\")\n        assert store.next_seq(\"b\") == 1\n\nclass TestAddedSince:\n    def test_strictly_after_boundary_excludes_equal_timestamp(self, store):\n        store.diff([job()])\n        ts = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()[\"first_seen\"]\n        assert store.added_since(ts) == []  # strict > per docstring\n\n    def test_ordered_oldest_first(self, store):\n        store.diff([job(external_id=\"1\")])\n        store.diff([job(external_id=\"2\")])\n        rows = store.added_since(\"2000-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\")\n        assert [r[\"external_id\"] for r in rows] == [\"1\", \"2\"]\n\nclass TestCount:\n    def test_count_reflects_rows(self, store):\n        assert store.count() == 0\n        store.diff([job()])\n        assert store.count() == 1\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `pipeline.py` — untested entirely: `load_config`, `run`, `run_sync`\n\nGaps:\n- `load_config` default injection (`sources`, `filters`, `db`, `concurrency`) when keys are absent from YAML.\n- `dry_run=True` returns `{\"matched\": N, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}` and never touches the store/dispatch (needs to be verified it doesn't call `Store` at all — currently would require patching).\n- Real run wires `fetch_all → filter_jobs → store.diff → dispatch` in the right order — an integration test with everything mocked/faked.\n- Malformed/missing YAML file raises appropriately (currently unhandled — `open()` raises `FileNotFoundError` uncaught, `yaml.safe_load` on empty file returns `None` and `cfg.setdefault` would crash on `None.setdefault`).\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import AsyncMock, patch\nfrom models import Job\nimport pipeline\n\nclass TestLoadConfig:\n    def test_defaults_filled_when_missing(self, tmp_path):\n        p = tmp_path / \"min.yaml\"\n        p.write_text(\"sources: []\\n\")\n        cfg = pipeline.load_config(p)\n        assert cfg[\"db\"] == \"jobs.db\"\n        assert cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 8\n        assert cfg[\"filters\"] == {}\n\n    def test_empty_yaml_file_raises_or_is_handled(self, tmp_path):\n        p = tmp_path / \"empty.yaml\"\n        p.write_text(\"\")\n        with pytest.raises(AttributeError):\n            pipeline.load_config(p)  # documents current crash on cfg=None\n\n    def test_missing_file_raises(self, tmp_path):\n        with pytest.raises(FileNotFoundError):\n            pipeline.load_config(tmp_path / \"nope.yaml\")\n\nclass TestRun:\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_dry_run_does_not_touch_store(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg_path = tmp_path / \"s.yaml\"\n        cfg_path.write_text(\"sources: []\\nfilters: {}\\n\")\n        with patch(\"pipeline.fetch_all\", new=AsyncMock(return_value=[\n                Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\",\n                    title=\"SWE\", url=\"u\")])), \\\n             patch(\"pipeline.Store\") as MockStore:\n            result = await pipeline.run(cfg_path, dry_run=True)\n            MockStore.assert_not_called()\n            assert result == {\"matched\": 1, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}\n\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_real_run_calls_dispatch_with_diff_output(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg_path = tmp_path / \"s.yaml\"\n        cfg_path.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path / 'j.db'}\\nsources: []\\nfilters: {{}}\\n\")\n        j = Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"SWE\", url=\"u\")\n        with patch(\"pipeline.fetch_all\", new=AsyncMock(return_value=[j])), \\\n             patch(\"pipeline.dispatch\") as mock_dispatch:\n            result = await pipeline.run(cfg_path, dry_run=False)\n            mock_dispatch.assert_called_once()\n            assert result[\"new\"] == 1\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. `notify.py` — untested entirely: all five notifiers + `dispatch`\n\nGaps:\n- Each notifier's env-var gate (missing var → no-op, no crash).\n- `notify_slack`/`notify_webhook`/`notify_email`/`notify_sms` should all **no-op silently** when there's nothing new/changed, even if env vars are set (avoid spam on empty runs).\n- `notify_email` requires `SMTP_HOST` **and** `EMAIL_TO`; partial config no-ops.\n- `notify_sms` requires **all four** Twilio vars; `resp.raise_for_status()` propagates on API failure — verify it's caught by `dispatch`, not by `notify_sms` itself.\n- `_sms_body` truncation at `limit=8` and the \"+N more\" line.\n- `dispatch` isolates failures: one notifier raising shouldn't stop the others from running.\n- `_line` formatting with/without `location`/`salary_range`.\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nimport httpx\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, MagicMock\nfrom models import Job\nimport notify\n\ndef job(**kw):\n    base = dict(source=\"x\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"SWE\", url=\"http://x\")\n    base.update(kw)\n    return Job(**base)\n\nclass TestNotifySlack:\n    def test_noop_without_env_var(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", raising=False)\n        with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\") as mock_post:\n            notify.notify_slack([job()], [])\n            mock_post.assert_not_called()\n\n    def test_noop_when_nothing_new_or_changed(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"http://hook\")\n        with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\") as mock_post:\n            notify.notify_slack([], [])\n            mock_post.assert_not_called()\n\n    def test_posts_when_configured_and_new_jobs(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"http://hook\")\n        with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\") as mock_post:\n            notify.notify_slack([job()], [])\n            mock_post.assert_called_once()\n\nclass TestNotifyEmail:\n    def test_noop_missing_email_to(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SMTP_HOST\", \"smtp.example.com\")\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"EMAIL_TO\", raising=False)\n        with patch(\"notify.smtplib.SMTP\") as mock_smtp:\n            notify.notify_email([job()], [])\n            mock_smtp.assert_not_called()\n\n    def test_sends_when_fully_configured(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SMTP_HOST\", \"smtp.example.com\")\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"EMAIL_TO\", \"me@example.com\")\n        smtp_instance = MagicMock()\n        with patch(\"notify.smtplib.SMTP\") as mock_smtp:\n            mock_smtp.return_value.__enter__.return_value = smtp_instance\n            notify.notify_email([job()], [])\n            smtp_instance.send_message.assert_called_once()\n\nclass TestNotifySms:\n    def test_noop_partial_twilio_config(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"sid\")\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", raising=False)\n        with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\") as mock_post:\n            notify.notify_sms([job()], [])\n            mock_post.assert_not_called()\n\n    def test_raises_on_twilio_error_status(self, monkeypatch):\n        for k, v in {\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\": \"sid\", \"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\": \"tok\",\n                      \"TWILIO_FROM\": \"+1\", \"TWILIO_TO\": \"+2\"}.items():\n            monkeypatch.setenv(k, v)\n        resp = httpx.Response(400, request=httpx.Request(\"POST\", \"http://x\"))\n        with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\", return_value=resp):\n            with pytest.raises(httpx.HTTPStatusError):\n                notify.notify_sms([job()], [])\n\nclass TestSmsBody:\n    def test_truncates_at_limit_with_more_count(self):\n        jobs = [job(external_id=str(i), title=f\"J{i}\") for i in range(12)]\n        body = notify._sms_body(jobs, [], limit=8)\n        assert \"+4 more\" in body\n        assert body.count(\"\\n- \") == 8\n\nclass TestDispatch:\n    def test_one_notifier_failing_does_not_block_others(self, capsys):\n        def boom(new, changed): raise RuntimeError(\"slack down\")\n        with patch.object(notify, \"NOTIFIERS\", [notify.notify_console, boom]):\n            notify.dispatch([job()], [])  # should not raise\n        assert \"notifier boom failed\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. `fetchers.py` — the largest gap. Untested: retry/backoff logic, every `parse_*` normalizer, every pagination loop, and the Meta/Google scraping edge cases.\n\nThis module is explicitly designed to be unit-testable via an injectable client (per its own docstring) — that intent is entirely unrealized right now.\n\n#### 6a. `_request` retry/backoff — highest priority, zero coverage\n\n```python\nimport httpx, pytest, respx\nfrom fetchers import _request, _get_json\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_retries_on_503_then_succeeds():\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with respx.mock(base_url=\"http://x\") as m:\n            route = m.get(\"/j\").mock(side_effect=[\n                httpx.Response(503), httpx.Response(200, json={\"ok\": True})])\n            r = await _request(client, \"http://x/j\", retries=3)\n            assert r.status_code == 200\n            assert route.call_count == 2\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_exhausts_retries_and_raises_runtime_error():\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with respx.mock(base_url=\"http://x\") as m:\n            m.get(\"/j\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(500))\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"failed to fetch\"):\n                await _request(client, \"http://x/j\", retries=2)\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_non_retryable_4xx_still_raises_after_first_attempt():\n    # 404 isn't in the retryable set but raise_for_status still fires\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with respx.mock(base_url=\"http://x\") as m:\n            route = m.get(\"/j\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(404))\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n                await _request(client, \"http://x/j\", retries=3)\n            assert route.call_count == 3  # documents: 404 is still retried via HTTPStatusError catch\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_transport_error_is_retried():\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with respx.mock(base_url=\"http://x\") as m:\n            m.get(\"/j\").mock(side_effect=httpx.ConnectTimeout(\"boom\"))\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n                await _request(client, \"http://x/j\", retries=2)\n```\n\n#### 6b. `parse_*` normalizers — pure functions, cheapest to test, currently 0 covered\n\nFor each: missing/optional fields, empty payload, and the documented quirky behavior.\n\n```python\nfrom fetchers import (parse_greenhouse, parse_lever, _lever_salary, parse_ashby,\n                       parse_smartrecruiters, parse_recruitee, parse_workable,\n                       parse_google, _extract_ds1, _ds1_posted_at, parse_deshaw,\n                       parse_twosigma, parse_optiver, parse_meta, parse_microsoft,\n                       parse_netflix, parse_amazon, _amazon_posted_at)\n\nclass TestParseGreenhouse:\n    def test_empty_jobs_list(self):\n        assert parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": []}) == []\n\n    def test_missing_location_and_departments_default_empty(self):\n        out = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"SWE\"}]})\n        assert out[0].location == \"\" and out[0].department == \"\"\n\n    def test_missing_id_raises_keyerror(self):\n        with pytest.raises(KeyError):\n            parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": [{\"title\": \"SWE\"}]})  # documents fragility\n\nclass TestLeverSalary:\n    def test_min_max_present_formats_range(self):\n        j = {\"salaryRange\": {\"min\": 100000, \"max\": 150000, \"currency\": \"USD\"}}\n        assert _lever_salary(j) == \"USD 100,000–150,000\"\n\n    def test_falls_back_to_description_when_no_range(self):\n        j = {\"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"Competitive\"}\n        assert _lever_salary(j) == \"Competitive\"\n\n    def test_no_salary_info_returns_empty_string(self):\n        assert _lever_salary({}) == \"\"\n\nclass TestParseAshby:\n    def test_unlisted_jobs_are_skipped(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"isListed\": False, \"title\": \"hidden\"}]}\n        assert parse_ashby(\"acme\", data) == []\n\nclass TestParseGoogleDs1:\n    def test_extract_ds1_missing_key_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _extract_ds1(\"<html>no data here</html>\") == []\n\n    def test_extract_ds1_malformed_json_returns_empty(self):\n        html = \"key: 'ds:1', data:[not valid json] , sideChannel\"\n        assert _extract_ds1(html) == []\n\n    def test_ds1_posted_at_prefers_create_time_index_12(self):\n        job = [None] * 15\n        job[12] = [1700000000, 0]\n        job[13] = [1800000000, 0]\n        assert _ds1_posted_at(job) != \"\"\n        # index 12 preferred over 13\n\n    def test_ds1_posted_at_no_timestamps_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _ds1_posted_at([None] * 5) == \"\"\n\n    def test_parse_google_skips_falsy_first_field(self):\n        assert parse_google(\"google\", [[None, \"Title\"]]) == []\n\nclass TestParseDeshaw:\n    def test_dedups_repeated_job_ids(self):\n        page = ('data-job-id=\"1\" class=\"job-display-name\">Eng<'\n                'data-job-id=\"1\" class=\"job-display-name\">Eng<')\n        out = parse_deshaw(\"deshaw\", page)\n        assert len(out) == 1\n\n    def test_unescapes_html_entities_in_title(self):\n        page = 'data-job-id=\"1\"class=\"job-display-name\">Eng&amp;Ops<'\n        out = parse_deshaw(\"deshaw\", page)\n        assert out[0].title == \"Eng&Ops\"\n\nclass TestParseTwosigma:\n    def test_dedups_triple_rendered_cards(self):\n        anchor = ('href=\"https://careers.twosigma.com/careers/JobDetail/foo/123\">'\n                   ' Quant Researcher </a>')\n        page = anchor * 3\n        out = parse_twosigma(\"twosigma\", page)\n        assert len(out) == 1\n\nclass TestParseOptiver:\n    def test_external_id_strips_join_us_jobs_prefix(self):\n        j = [{\"href\": \"/join-us/jobs/eng/ams/swe-123\", \"title\": \"SWE\"}]\n        out = parse_optiver(\"optiver\", j)\n        assert out[0].external_id == \"eng/ams/swe-123\"\n\n    def test_absolute_href_used_as_is(self):\n        j = [{\"href\": \"https://external.example.com/job/1\", \"title\": \"SWE\"}]\n        out = parse_optiver(\"optiver\", j)\n        assert out[0].url == \"https://external.example.com/job/1\"\n\nclass TestParseMeta:\n    def test_dedups_by_id(self):\n        results = [{\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"A\"}, {\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"A-dup\"}]\n        out = parse_meta(\"meta\", results)\n        assert len(out) == 1\n\n    def test_missing_id_skipped(self):\n        assert parse_meta(\"meta\", [{\"title\": \"no id\"}]) == []\n\nclass TestAmazonPostedAt:\n    def test_valid_us_date(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"June 26, 2026\") == \"2026-06-26T00:00:00+00:00\"\n\n    def test_malformed_date_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"not a date\") == \"\"\n\n    def test_unknown_month_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"Xxxday 1, 2026\") == \"\"\n\nclass TestParseMicrosoft:\n    def test_posted_ts_converted_to_iso(self):\n        out = parse_microsoft(\"ms\", [{\"id\": \"1\", \"name\": \"SWE\", \"postedTs\": 1700000000}])\n        assert out[0].posted_at.startswith(\"20\")\n\n    def test_missing_posted_ts_blank(self):\n        out = parse_microsoft(\"ms\", [{\"id\": \"1\", \"name\": \"SWE\"}])\n        assert out[0].posted_at == \"\"\n```\n\n#### 6c. Pagination loops (`fetch_twosigma`, `fetch_optiver`, `fetch_workday`, `fetch_google`, `fetch_microsoft`, `fetch_netflix`, `fetch_amazon`) — none tested\n\nShared pattern to verify: stop-on-empty-batch, dedup across pages, `max_pages` safety cap actually caps.\n\n```python\nimport respx, httpx, pytest\nfrom fetchers import fetch_optiver, fetch_workday, fetch_google\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_optiver_stops_when_no_fresh_items():\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with respx.mock(base_url=\"https://www.optiver.com\") as m:\n            m.get(\"/en/api/v1/jobs\").mock(side_effect=[\n                httpx.Response(200, json={\"items\": [{\"href\": \"/join-us/jobs/a\", \"title\": \"A\"}]}),\n                httpx.Response(200, json={\"items\": []}),\n            ])\n            jobs = await fetch_optiver(client, {\"company\": \"optiver\", \"max_pages\": 5})\n            assert len(jobs) == 1\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_optiver_respects_max_pages_cap():\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with respx.mock(base_url=\"https://www.optiver.com\") as m:\n            m.get(\"/en/api/v1/jobs\").mock(\n                return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\n                    \"items\": [{\"href\": f\"/join-us/jobs/{i}\", \"title\": \"A\"} for i in range(16)]}))\n            jobs = await fetch_optiver(client, {\"company\": \"optiver\", \"max_pages\": 2})\n            # each page returns 16 \"fresh\" distinct-looking hrefs by index... verify call count capped\n            assert m[\"jobs\"].call_count <= 2\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_workday_stops_at_total_or_safety_cap():\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with respx.mock() as m:\n            m.post(\"https://h.myworkdayjobs.com/wday/cxs/t/s/jobs\").mock(\n                return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobPostings\": [], \"total\": 0}))\n            jobs = await fetch_workday(client, {\"host\": \"h.myworkdayjobs.com\",\n                                                  \"tenant\": \"t\", \"site\": \"s\"})\n            assert jobs == []\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_google_stops_on_empty_page():\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with respx.mock(base_url=\"https://www.google.com\") as m:\n            m.get(\"/about/careers/applications/jobs/results/\").mock(\n                return_value=httpx.Response(200, text=\"<html>no ds:1 data</html>\"))\n            jobs = await fetch_google(client, {\"company\": \"google\", \"max_pages\": 3})\n            assert jobs == []\n```\n\n#### 6d. `fetch_meta` — special-cased doc_id rotation error path, untested\n\n```python\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_meta_raises_readable_error_on_graphql_errors():\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with respx.mock(base_url=\"https://www.metacareers.com\") as m:\n            m.get(\"/jobs\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(200, text=\"<html></html>\"))\n            m.post(\"/graphql\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(\n                200, text='for (;;);{\"errors\":[{\"message\":\"doc_id rotated\"}]}'))\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"doc_id rotated\"):\n                await fetch_meta(client, {\"company\": \"meta\"})\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_meta_strips_for_loop_prefix():\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with respx.mock(base_url=\"https://www.metacareers.com\") as m:\n            m.get(\"/jobs\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(200, text=\"<html></html>\"))\n            body = '{\"data\":{\"job_search_with_featured_jobs_v2\":{\"all_jobs\":[]}}}'\n            m.post(\"/graphql\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(200, text=f\"for (;;);{body}\"))\n            jobs = await fetch_meta(client, {\"company\": \"meta\"})\n            assert jobs == []\n```\n\n#### 6e. `fetch_source` and `fetch_all` — the top-level dispatcher, untested\n\n```python\nfrom fetchers import fetch_source, fetch_all\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_source_unknown_ats_raises_valueerror():\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n            await fetch_source(client, {\"ats\": \"bogus_ats\"})\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_all_one_source_failing_does_not_kill_others():\n    good = Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"a\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"T\", url=\"u\")\n    async def one_side_effect(src):\n        if src[\"ats\"] == \"broken\":\n            raise RuntimeError(\"boom\")\n        return [good]\n    with patch(\"fetchers.fetch_source\", side_effect=one_side_effect):\n        jobs = await fetch_all([{\"ats\": \"broken\"}, {\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"a\"}])\n        assert jobs == [good]\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_all_respects_concurrency_semaphore():\n    # verify at most `concurrency` in-flight calls via a counting side effect\n    ...\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. `agent.py` — untested entirely: `cmd_db_new`, `cmd_db_mark`, `cmd_report_num`, `_normalize_ats`, `cmd_pdf_render`, `_chrome_bin`, `main` routing\n\nGaps:\n- `cmd_db_new` group-boundary truncation logic (`groupby` on `first_seen`) — the comment explicitly says it must never split a timestamp group; this invariant is unverified.\n- `cmd_db_new` first-run vs. marker-exists branching.\n- `cmd_db_mark` rejects non-ISO watermark with exit code 2; accepts `--now`; requires one of `watermark`/`--now`.\n- `_normalize_ats` must skip replacements inside `<style>`/`<script>` tags and inside tag attributes (only touches text nodes) — this is subtle regex-based HTML handling, currently unverified.\n- `_chrome_bin` discovery order: `CHROME_PATH` env → `PATH` lookup → hardcoded app paths → `sys.exit`.\n- `main()` argv routing (`db-new`, `db-mark`, `pdf-render`, `report-num`, bare invocation → interactive, mode words vs. flags split).\n\n```python\nimport pytest, json\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, MagicMock\nfrom models import Job\nimport agent\nfrom store import Store\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef cfg(tmp_path):\n    p = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    p.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path / 'jobs.db'}\\nsources: []\\n\")\n    return str(p)\n\nclass TestCmdDbNew:\n    def test_first_run_uses_since_days_window(self, cfg, capsys):\n        agent.cmd_db_new([\"-c\", cfg, \"--since-days\", \"3\"])\n        out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n        assert out[\"first_run\"] is True\n        assert out[\"count\"] == 0\n\n    def test_never_splits_a_first_seen_group_at_limit_boundary(self, cfg, capsys):\n        with Store(cfg.replace(\"sources.yaml\", \"jobs.db\")) if False else Store(\n                agent.load_config(cfg)[\"db\"]) as store:\n            same_ts_jobs = [Job(source=\"x\", company=\"c\", external_id=str(i),\n                                 title=\"T\", url=\"u\") for i in range(5)]\n            store.diff(same_ts_jobs)  # all land with identical first_seen\n        agent.cmd_db_new([\"-c\", cfg, \"--limit\", \"3\"])  # limit smaller than the group\n        out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n        # group must be kept whole even though it exceeds --limit, per docstring\n        assert out[\"count\"] == 5 or out[\"truncated\"] is False\n\nclass TestCmdDbMark:\n    def test_rejects_non_iso_watermark(self, cfg, capsys):\n        rc = agent.cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-date\", \"-c\", cfg])\n        assert rc == 2\n\n    def test_now_flag_sets_current_time(self, cfg):\n        rc = agent.cmd_db_mark([\"--now\", \"-c\", cfg])\n        assert rc == 0\n\n    def test_no_args_returns_error(self, cfg):\n        rc = agent.cmd_db_mark([\"-c\", cfg])\n        assert rc == 2\n\nclass TestNormalizeAts:\n    def test_em_dash_replaced_in_text(self):\n        html, counts = agent._normalize_ats(\"<p>a\\u2014b</p>\")\n        assert \"a-b\" in html and counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1\n\n    def test_style_block_untouched(self):\n        html, counts = agent._normalize_ats(\n            \"<style>.x::before{content:'\\u2014'}</style><p>\\u2014</p>\")\n        assert \"\\u2014\" in html.split(\"</style>\")[0]\n        assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1  # only the <p> occurrence counted\n\n    def test_script_block_untouched(self):\n        html, counts = agent._normalize_ats(\n            \"<script>var x='\\u2014';</script><p>ok</p>\")\n        assert \"\\u2014\" in html.split(\"</script>\")[0]\n\n    def test_tag_attributes_untouched(self):\n        html, counts = agent._normalize_ats('<a title=\"\\u2014\">text</a>')\n        assert 'title=\"\\u2014\"' in html\n\nclass TestChromeBin:\n    def test_env_var_used_when_exists(self, tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n        fake = tmp_path / \"chrome\"\n        fake.write_text(\"\")\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"CHROME_PATH\", str(fake))\n        assert agent._chrome_bin() == str(fake)\n\n    def test_exits_when_nothing_found(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"CHROME_PATH\", raising=False)\n        with patch(\"shutil.which\", return_value=None), \\\n             patch(\"pathlib.Path.exists\", return_value=False):\n            with pytest.raises(SystemExit):\n                agent._chrome_bin()\n\nclass TestMainRouting:\n    def test_routes_to_db_new(self):\n        with patch(\"agent.cmd_db_new\", return_value=0) as m:\n            agent.main.__wrapped__ if False else None\n            with patch(\"sys.argv\", [\"agent.py\", \"db-new\"]):\n                agent.main()\n            m.assert_called_once()\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. `cli.py` — untested\n\n```python\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nimport cli\n\ndef test_cli_passes_dry_run_flag_through():\n    with patch(\"cli.run_sync\") as mock_run:\n        with patch(\"sys.argv\", [\"cli.py\", \"--dry-run\", \"-c\", \"sources.yaml\"]):\n            cli.main()\n        mock_run.assert_called_once_with(\"sources.yaml\", dry_run=True)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Integration test gaps (no single unit test covers these)\n\n1. **End-to-end pipeline**: config → fake fetchers → filter → store.diff → dispatch, asserting the final printed summary line and returned dict, using a real (tmp file) SQLite store rather than mocking `Store`.\n2. **Re-run idempotency**: run the pipeline twice against the same DB with identical fetch output — second run must report `new: 0, changed: 0`.\n3. **Cross-module dedup key stability**: a job whose `title` changes between two fetches from the *same* company/external_id is classified `changed`, not `new`+orphaned-old-row.\n4. **`agent.py db-new` → `db-mark` workflow**: dump jobs, mark the returned `watermark` (not `--now`), re-dump — previously-dumped jobs must not reappear, and jobs written *during* the dump window (between watermark and now) must not be silently skipped.\n5. **Notifier fan-out with mixed success/failure**: one notifier configured and failing (e.g., bad Slack URL) must not prevent SMS from firing.\n\n### Missing error-handling tests (highest-value, currently absent)\n\n| Function | Untested failure mode |\n|---|---|\n| `fetch_all` → `one()` | any exception from `fetch_source` is swallowed and logged — never asserted |\n| `_request` | retry exhaustion → `RuntimeError` wrapping the last exception — never asserted |\n| `pipeline.load_config` | missing file / empty YAML — currently would raise unhandled `FileNotFoundError`/`AttributeError` |\n| `notify.notify_sms` | Twilio 4xx/5xx → `raise_for_status()` propagates out of `notify_sms` but is caught by `dispatch` — the boundary between \"notifier-level\" and \"dispatch-level\" error handling is unverified |\n| `agent.cmd_pdf_render` | Chrome binary produces non-PDF output (`data.startswith(b\"%PDF\")` check) → return code 1, stderr tail printed — never exercised |\n| `store.Store.__init__` | opening a corrupt/non-SQLite file at the given path |\n| `fetchers.parse_greenhouse` et al. | missing required key (e.g. `j[\"id\"]`) → `KeyError` propagates uncaught up through `fetch_all`'s try/except — worth an explicit test documenting that a single malformed record kills that whole source's batch |\n\n### Priority order if implementing incrementally\n\n1. `store.py` (dedup correctness is the core value prop) and `filters.py` (pure, cheap, high bug-risk from regex/word-boundary logic).\n2. `models.py` (`parse_posted_at` boundary conditions feed directly into filtering).\n3. `fetchers.py` parse functions (pure, no I/O, highest function count).\n4. `fetchers.py` retry/pagination (needs `respx`, more setup but protects against silent data loss on ATS changes).\n5. `notify.py` and `pipeline.py` (mostly orchestration/env-var glue).\n6. `agent.py` (CLI glue, `_normalize_ats` regex correctness is the one piece worth real scrutiny).\n",
